# Enterprise Procurement & Supply Record-Keeping System (SRKS)

This repository contains the complete source code and architectural blueprints for **SRKS**, a high-performance, legally compliant procurement and logistics tracking system designed for heavy industrial supply chains (e.g., Dangote Group operations).

SRKS enforces strict role-based access control, automated double-entry accounting (3-Way Match), and cryptographic document verification to eliminate procurement fraud and streamline physical supply deliveries.

---

## 🏗️ Core Technology Stack

* **Frontend:** Next.js 15 (App Router), React, Tailwind CSS, Shadcn/ui
* **Backend:** Next.js Server Actions (Bypassing traditional REST endpoints for lower latency)
* **Database & Auth:** Supabase (PostgreSQL, GoTrue Auth, Storage, Supavisor Edge Networking)
* **Security & Cryptography:** Native Web Crypto API (SHA-256), Vercel Edge Middleware
* **Document Generation:** jsPDF, QRCode

---

## 📑 System Modules Overview

The application is split into two heavily isolated environments, governed by Edge Middleware to prevent unauthorized access.

### 1. Management Module (Admin)

The control center for corporate finance and procurement managers.

* **Master Product Vault:** Define catalog items, units of measure, and compliance variables (7.5% VAT, 5%/10% WHT).
* **Two-Stage PO Factory:** * *Stage 1:* Create "Shell" purchase orders detailing required items and delivery destinations.
* *Stage 2:* Activate POs by locking in negotiated prices, assigning vendors, and defining logistics routing (Vendor vs. 3PL).


* **Financial Ledgers & Match Station:** Live dashboard tracking Accounts Payable (AP), Accounts Receivable (AR), and a variance-resolution station for flagging operational discrepancies.

### 2. Operations Module (Agent)

The execution layer built for field agents and logistics officers operating at ports or delivery yards.

* **Active Pipeline Kanban:** A simplified, read-only view of active orders assigned to the field. Prices are intentionally hidden.
* **Chronological Document Hub:** A strictly gated upload interface:
* Agents upload Supplier Invoices.
* Agents upload Vendor Dispatch Waybills.
* **Logic Gate:** The system only unlocks the internal *Outbound Company Waybill* download once the Vendor Waybill is verified.
* Agents upload the final signed client Goods Received Note (GRN) to close the loop.



---

## ⚙️ The Automated 3-Way Match Engine

To ensure zero financial leakage, SRKS runs an automated reconciliation algorithm via a Supabase Remote Procedure Call (RPC) the moment the final GRN is uploaded by an Agent.

* **Success Path:** If the invoiced volumes and prices match the Admin's locked PO terms, the system automatically initializes a double-entry ledger track, crediting the Vendor (and 3PL if applicable) and debiting the Customer account. The PO is locked as `reconciled`.
* **Variance Path:** If a mismatch is detected, the transaction freezes. The PO is marked as `variance_hold` and flagged on the Admin dashboard for manual override or credit-note resolution.

---

## 🔐 Security & Governance Features

### 1. Cryptographic Document Verification

All PDFs generated by the system (e.g., Company Outbound Waybills) are stamped with a Base64 QR code and a **SHA-256 cryptographic hash** of the order payload. This ensures physical paper documents cannot be altered at delivery gates without failing a digital verification scan.

### 2. Immutable System Audit Log

A core database trigger (`FOR EACH STATEMENT`) guards the `system_audit_log` table. It immediately rejects any `UPDATE`, `DELETE`, or `TRUNCATE` commands. Every critical action (like overriding a variance hold) writes a permanent JSON manifest to this table.

### 3. Edge Route Protection (RBAC)

Next.js `middleware.ts` runs on the Vercel Edge, introspecting Supabase session cookies before pages render. Agents attempting to visit `/admin` routes (or vice versa) are instantly bounced to their correct dashboards, shielding serverless functions from execution overhead.

---

## 🚀 Local Setup & Installation

### Prerequisites

* Node.js 18+
* A free [Supabase](https://supabase.com/) account and project.

### 1. Clone & Install

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-org/srks-system.git
cd srks-system
npm install

```

### 2. Supabase Database & Storage Configuration

1. Open your Supabase SQL Editor and execute the **Unified Architecture & Seed Engine SQL script** provided in the TRD. This builds all tables, triggers, policies, and inserts deterministic Nigerian enterprise test data.
2. Navigate to **Storage** in your Supabase dashboard.
3. Create a public bucket exactly named: `procurement-docs`.

### 3. Environment Variables

Create a `.env.local` file in the root directory and add your Supabase credentials:

```env
# Supabase Configuration
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL="https://[YOUR_PROJECT_ID].supabase.co"
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY="[YOUR_ANON_KEY]"
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY="[YOUR_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY]" # Never expose to the browser

# Application Base
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL="http://localhost:3000"

```

### 4. Run the Development Server

```bash
npm run dev

```

Access the application at `http://localhost:3000`.

**Test Accounts (from Seed Data):**

* **Admin Role:** User tied to ID `00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001`
* **Agent Role:** User tied to ID `00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002`
*(Note: You will need to create these users in the Supabase Auth dashboard to match the seeded UUIDs for logging in).*

---

## 📂 Project Directory Map

* `/app/(auth)` - Login gateway
* `/app/admin` - Management dashboards (Products, PO Factory, Ledgers)
* `/app/agent` - Operational pipelines and document hubs
* `/components/ui` - Shadcn primitive UI elements
* `/components/shared` - Cross-module components (e.g., PDF Download Button)
* `/lib/actions` - Next.js Server Actions (Auth, Admin, Agent backend logic)
* `/lib/supabase` - SSR client configurations
* `/lib/utils` - Cryptography and jsPDF generation scripts